Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  John Vaughn is sworn to interpret for the defendant via zoom. The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crime of operate under influence (4th).  The matter is continued for initial appearance on 01-24-22 at 1:30 p.m.  Bail is set at $1,500.00 cash bond with the conditions that he report to the Manitowoc City Police Department for fingerprints, photographs and identifying information within 48 hours or, if incarcerated, within 72 hours of release, defendant is not to operate a motor vehicle and defendant must maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol and drugs  Bail not furnished and defendant is remanded to the custody of the Sheriff.
